### Video Player with Optimistic Progress
```svelte
<script>
  import { updateProgress } from '$lib/collections/library';

  let { data } = $props();
  let videoEl: HTMLVideoElement;
  let saveTimer: number;

  // Debounced progress save (every 5 seconds)
  function handleTimeUpdate() {
    clearTimeout(saveTimer);
    saveTimer = setTimeout(() => {
      updateProgress(
        data.content.id,
        videoEl.currentTime,
        videoEl.duration
      );
      // UI updates IMMEDIATELY (optimistic)
      // Server sync happens in background via onUpdate
    }, 5000);
  }

  // Save on pause/close
  function handlePause() {
    clearTimeout(saveTimer);
    updateProgress(
      data.content.id,
      videoEl.currentTime,
      videoEl.duration
    );
  }
</script>

<video
  bind:this={videoEl}
  src={data.streamingUrl}
  ontimeupdate={handleTimeUpdate}
  onpause={handlePause}
/>
```

## Key Concepts

### Optimistic Updates Flow
```
User action (seek video)
       │
       ▼
collection.update()
       │
       ├──► UI updates IMMEDIATELY (optimistic)
       │
       ▼
onUpdate handler called
       │
       ├──► savePlaybackProgress() to server
       │
       ├─── Success: done
       │
       └─── Failure: AUTOMATIC ROLLBACK
                     UI reverts to previous state
```

### Draft Updates (Immer-style)
```typescript
libraryCollection.update(contentId, (draft) => {
  // Mutate draft directly - TanStack DB handles immutability
  draft.progress.positionSeconds = 120;
  draft.progress.completed = true;
});
```

### Error Handling
- If `onUpdate` throws, transaction rolls back automatically
- UI reverts to previous state
- Error can be caught for user notification

